   - Test list phase via `Skill({ skill: "test-list" })`
   - Red phase via `Skill({ skill: "red" })` with two-stage predictions (compile error + runtime error), MUST output exact "Correct/Incorrect" format for metric parsing
   - Green phase via `Skill({ skill: "green" })` with minimal implementation
   - Refactor phase via `Task({ subagent_type: "refactor", ... })` — never refactor in main context
   - Continue autonomously without HITL
   - When all tests pass, write `experiment-done.txt` with just `DONE`

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - TypeScript with strict types, ES modules (".js" import extensions)
   - Vitest testing framework (`pnpm test`)
   - TDD Red-Green-Refactor with predictions
   - Simple Design Rules (Tests Pass, Reveals Intent, No Duplication, Fewest Elements)
   - APP (Absolute Priority Premise) mass analysis
   - Insurance domain: per-item modifiers (cursed, high-enchantment), policy-level modifiers (loyalty, first-insurance, follow-up), block-of-3 component discount
